The European Community's annualinflation rate fell marginally to 3.2 pct in May from 3.3 pctin April, the EC's statistics office Eurostat said.    Prices in the 12-nation bloc rose 0.2 pct in May after 0.6pct in April. But the annual rate stayed below that of the U.S.For the second month in succession, following the release offigures showing U.S. Inflation of 3.8 pct in both April andMay.    However, Eurostat said the EC was still beaten by Japan,where prices were provisionally 0.1 pct lower in May than ayear earlier. REUTER&#3;